                <pb n="1"/>
                <p>Rev&#58; Dr S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia Pa.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev&#58; Sir&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>In my capacity of modern Hazan<lb/> I have found to my regret the scar&#45;<lb/>city of good English translations<lb/> of some parts of the ritual&#44; particu&#45;<lb/>larly of such adopted for musical<lb/> compositions.  For the last Simchath<lb/> Torah festival I have composed<lb/> a Contata&#44; a somewhat elaborate<lb/> composition&#44; to the Hebrew words&#58;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; ending with &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> etc &#91;Hebrew&#93;.  To this whole&#44; rather lengthy<lb/> Hymn&#44; I have no English translation<lb/> at all.  Intending to publish the music<lb/> I would not like to do so without<lb/> adding to it an English version.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I therefore take the liberty to<lb/> kindly request you to assist me<lb/> in getting the English translation<lb/> metrically corresponding<lb/> with the Hebrew text.  Knowing<lb/> that you or some of your literary<lb/> <sic>aquaintances</sic> are able to ac&#45;<lb/>complish this&#44; by no means&#44;<lb/> easy task&#44; I trust that you<lb/> will kindly aid me by com&#45;<lb/>plying with the request<lb/> of yours<lb/> most respectfully<lb/> A Kaiser<lb/> Baltimore Dec. 20. 1887.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>A. KAISER&#44;<lb/>
                No. 23 HOLLINS STREET&#44;<lb/>
                BALTIMORE&#44; MD.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
